General.Name: George Kent (Malaysia) Bhd
General.Description: George Kent (Malaysia) Berhad, an engineering company, engages in the rail transportation, water infrastructure, and hospital construction business in Malaysia. The company manufactures and supplies water meters, brass components, valves, waterworks fittings, and flow control tools for residential, industrial, and commercial customers. It is also involved in the construction of water infrastructure and hospital projects; systems work for rail transportation; and operation and maintenance services for water treatment facilities. In addition, the company exports its products to Singapore, Hong Kong, Thailand, Vietnam, Myanmar, Cambodia, Indonesia, the Philippines, Nepal, Papua New Guinea, Australia, India, Sri Lanka, Kenya, South Africa, South America, the United Kingdom, and internationally. George Kent (Malaysia) Berhad was founded in 1936 and is based in Puchong, Malaysia.
